<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-265-043 </DOCNO><DOCID>08 723 250</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Desktop Publishing  July 16 1990 v4 n11p40(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Company news. (Ventura Software Inc.)(Adobe Systems acquiresBluePoint Technologies)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adobe Systems Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)BluePoint Technologies (acquisitions and mergers)Xerox Desktop Software Inc. (names)Ventura Software Inc. (names).andO;Ticker:    ADBE.andO;Topic:     AcquisitionSoftware PublishersSubsidiary Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Xerox Desktop Software, a subsidiary of Xerox Corporation, has been renamedVentura Software Inc. and has moved to a new location.andP;  Although the Xeroxsubsidiary sells other products, Ventura Publisher is its bread and butter.andO;Xerox evidently hopes that some of Ventura's cachet will rub off on FormBaseand perhaps even the moribund Pc versions of Cricket Draw and Cricket Graph.andM;Ventura Software's new address is 15175 Innovation Drive, San Diego, CA92128; phone (619) 673-7537.andM;Adobe Systems has acquired BluePoint Technologies, which makes the BP100A, achip for rendering hinted outline fonts.andP;  Adobe said that it would useBluePomes technology to create a chip for the Adobe Type I font format.andP;  Sucha chip would be incorporated into future Adobe Post-Script controller designsand licensed to OEMS.andM;Adobe declined to set a timetable for chip production.andP;  It did promise tosupport existing BP100A products and honor BluePoint's OEM contracts.andO;</TEXT></DOC>